cyclone.name: HUMBERTO
cyclone.current_location: about 130 mi ESE of Great Abaco Island
cyclone.trajectory: moving northwest then turning north-northwest, expected to pass just offshore the east-central Florida coast and then head northward parallel to the Southeast U.S. shoreline
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: None – forecast to remain offshore of Florida

weather_observation.watch_coast: None in effect along Florida coast
weather_observation.warning_coast: None in effect along Florida coast (warnings limited to north-western Bahamas)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Atlantic coast from central Florida northward to the Carolinas likely to experience rain, gusty winds and high surf
weather_observation.rain_fall_above_4_inch: Possible but not likely; forecast totals generally 2-4 inches
weather_observation.wind: Low-to-moderate chance (≤29%) of sustained tropical-storm-force winds; brief gusts 40–50 mph possible Sunday
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor coastal flooding and dangerous rip currents possible, but significant surge (>3 ft) not expected
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands of heavy rain could deliver 2–4 inches Saturday night through Sunday with isolated higher pockets
weather_observation.other_hazards: High surf and life-threatening rip currents beginning late Saturday
